cbank (cli) changes

 * modified report columns to maintain consistency with 0.2 reports (#220)
 * admins and project owners can see all charges to a project with -p (#218)
 * improved report option behavior based on admin feedback (#219)

-- 0.3.1 --

clusterbank (api) changes

 * mapped Allocation.amount_charged to a query
 * Project.charge performs a distributed charge
 * Charge.transfer refunds a charge and re-applies it as charges to a project
 * fixed a bug where clusterbank.model configured independently

cbank (cli) changes

 * date options can now accept times
 * restored ability to display comments inline
 * charge report reflects refunds in charge amount
 * added '-n' flag to cbank-new scripts
 * fixed a bug that caused the detail view to crash on charges with refunds
 * deprecated '-m' in favor of '-c' in cbank-new scripts
 * fixed implementation of admin permissions (#216)

-- 0.3.0 --

clusterbank (api) changes

 * removed _table suffix from table objects in clusterbank.model.database
 * consolidated configuration at clusterbank.config
 * user, project, and resource __str__ returns entity name
 * user, project, and resource __repr__ include entity name
 * moved mapper-aware code from clusterbank.model.entities to clusterbank.model
 * <Entity>.by_name has become clusterbank.model.<entity>_by_name
 * moved from Session.mapper to mapper

cbank (cli) changes

 * added commands to create a new allocation, hold, charge, or refund
 * adopted a formal metacommand dispatch architecture (new, report, detail)
 * removed usage report
 * "projects" returns to the default report
 * "projects", "allocations", and "charges" reports redesigned (again)
 * added a "holds" report
 * added a "users" report
 * rebase reports outside the ORM for better performance until SA 0.5
 * improved error messages
 * cbank errors provide distinct error codes
 * changed multi-value options from comma-separated lists to multi-options
 * added shell-level entry points for all cbank commands

-- 0.2.15.1 --

 * fixed a refund accounting bug in the cbank project report (r459)

-- 0.2.15 --

 * moved SQLAlchemy version dependency to 0.4.5
 * fixed date ranges in the projects report
 * require charges to exist within their allocation
 * moved the example upstream module into clusterbank as a default
 * added autoconfiguration to the default upstream module
 * added cbank examples to clusterbank.conf.sample
 * renamed upstream package to upstreams to avoid name collision
 * added a "total" line to the cbank allocation report
 * widened the "amount" column in the cbank charge report
 * added an additional example in the cbank manpage
 * added start date to the cbank allocation report (in --extra-data)
 * removed arbitrary restrictions on admin reports
 * removed cbank_old
 * added a new report, "usage" (also available as "use")

-- 0.2.14 --

 * corrected cbank error handling for unknown user
 * made project report the default cbank report
 * removed old cbank testsuite
 * defined a base exception for clusterbank
 * added date ranges (--after, --before) to cbank
 * entity filters are now csv-plural (--users, --projects, --resources)
 * added admins to cbank
 * added user column to cbank charge report
 * added the --extra-data flag to cbank (displays comment field)
 * documented cbank in a manpage
 * documented the upstream interface

-- 0.2.13 --

 * updated the upstream example for the new upstream interface
 * replaced cbank2 with a more user-friendly version

-- 0.2.12 --

 * cbank can transform displayed and interpreted units
 * config file can specify a default recource for cbank
 * fixed bugs in cbank filters
 * added headers to cbank
 * display date charged in cbank
 * cbank gives a usage message on error
 * cbank filters by current user by default
 * admin privilege management in cbank
 * charges and holds can have an associated user
 * added users to the upstream interface
 * simplified the upstream interface
 * changed upstream module interface to functions only (#133)

-- 0.2.11 --

 * cbank displays amount remaining in allocation
 * cbank enters the current time (by default) when creating an allocation (#126)
 * removed the default datetime from the credit_limits table
 * moved upstream example out of the packages directory
 * merged accounting.py into entities.py (#122)
 * better help output (#114)
 * only require configuration when necessary (#130)
 * better declaration of required options in cbank (#128)
 * cbank displays entity details using formatting functions
 * cbank queries (-l) more intuitive through abstract base queries and filters
 * rewrote cbank mostly from the ground up
 * (very) minor testsuite cleanup (still needs a lot more)
 * removed legacy upstream data from clusterbank.conf.sample

-- 0.2.10 --

 * simplified upstream module loading (#116)
 * userbase module replaced with upstream_example (not distributed)
 * remove inner-class exception stupidness (#119)
 * check compatibility with SA 0.4.0
 * allow charges to make a project go negative (#117)
 * move to session extensions for application-side integrity constraints (#118)
 * fix two broken tests around RemainingAmount (#120)
 * use nose tools to test exceptions (#110)

